# Local Context — host-specific configuration

This file is **gitignored**. It contains environment-specific URLs, IDs, and
references that should never be committed to the repo. Copy this template to
`.claude/local-context.md` and fill in the real values for your workspace:

```bash
cp .claude/local-context.md.example .claude/local-context.md
# then edit .claude/local-context.md with your real Notion URLs / IDs
```

The orchestrator backend automatically appends the contents of
`.claude/local-context.md` to the merged `CLAUDE.md` written into each session
worktree, so dashboard-launched sessions see the same context as Claude Code
sessions opened directly in this repo.

